1
00:00:04,254 --> 00:00:07,633
ANNOUNCER: The Ood,
they came from a distant world.

2
00:00:07,758 --> 00:00:12,638
They voyaged across the stars,
all with one purpose.

3
00:00:12,930 --> 00:00:14,973
Do you take milk and sugar?

4
00:00:15,098 --> 00:00:16,183
10 serve.

5
00:00:16,266 --> 00:00:18,894
No, that's good. Uh, that's excellent.

6
00:00:18,977 --> 00:00:22,397
I like it, sir. "Buy one now."
Direct, straight to the point.

7
00:00:22,481 --> 00:00:24,900
MAN ON INTERCOM: We play that across
the trigalactic for two weeks,

8
00:00:24,983 --> 00:00:26,693
then introduce this.

9
00:00:26,777 --> 00:00:28,904
ANNOUNCER: Now only 50 credits.

10
00:00:28,987 --> 00:00:32,032
Fifty?
We're reducing the price to 50 credits?

11
00:00:32,115 --> 00:00:36,078
Sales are down. We've got to
reposition ourselves. So get going.

12
00:00:36,161 --> 00:00:38,789
Idiot. Bleeding us dry.

13
00:00:39,790 --> 00:00:42,751
You there, get me last month's
military export figures.

14
00:00:42,834 --> 00:00:45,462
The army always need more grunts.

15
00:00:45,546 --> 00:00:47,130
Yes, sir.

16
00:00:47,798 --> 00:00:50,634
RECEPTIONIST ON INTERCOM:
Mr Bartle, you asked me to call you.

17
00:00:50,801 --> 00:00:54,263
Solana, when those buyers arrive,
we're going to pitch like never before.

18
00:00:54,346 --> 00:00:57,015
I want those Ood flying out of here.

19
00:00:58,809 --> 00:01:01,937
That... I said military figures.
That's the domestic file.

20
00:01:02,020 --> 00:01:03,939
Get me the military.

21
00:01:04,648 --> 00:01:06,316
The file is irrelevant, sir.

22
00:01:06,400 --> 00:01:08,235
Oh? And why's that?

23
00:01:10,153 --> 00:01:11,822
Have a nice day.

24
00:01:13,115 --> 00:01:15,576
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

25
00:01:51,862 --> 00:01:53,947
(DONNA SCREAMING)

26
00:01:58,410 --> 00:02:01,038
Set the controls for random.
Mystery tour.

27
00:02:01,121 --> 00:02:05,584
Outside that door could be any planet,
anywhere, any when in the whole wide...

28
00:02:05,709 --> 00:02:08,211
-Are you all right?
-Terrified.

29
00:02:08,337 --> 00:02:11,632
I mean, history's one thing,
but an alien planet!

30
00:02:11,715 --> 00:02:14,551
-I could always take you home.
-Yeah, don't laugh at me.

31
00:02:14,676 --> 00:02:18,221
I know what it's like,
everything you're feeling right now.

32
00:02:18,305 --> 00:02:20,557
Fear, the joy, the wonder, I get that!

33
00:02:20,641 --> 00:02:22,809
Seriously? After all this time?

34
00:02:22,893 --> 00:02:24,728
Yeah! Why do you think I keep going?

35
00:02:24,811 --> 00:02:27,689
Oh! All right, then, you and me both.

36
00:02:28,398 --> 00:02:30,233
This is barmy!

37
00:02:30,692 --> 00:02:32,277
I was born in Chiswick.

38
00:02:32,361 --> 00:02:35,197
I've only ever done package holidays
and now I'm here.

39
00:02:35,280 --> 00:02:37,949
This is... It's not... I mean, it's...

40
00:02:38,033 --> 00:02:42,371
I don't know, it's all sort of...
I don't even know what the word is!

41
00:02:46,750 --> 00:02:48,502
I've got the word.

42
00:02:49,211 --> 00:02:50,587
Freezing.

43
00:02:51,254 --> 00:02:52,923
Snow!

44
00:02:53,048 --> 00:02:56,468
Ah, real snow. Proper snow at last.

45
00:02:56,593 --> 00:02:58,970
That's more like it. Lovely.
What do you think?

46
00:02:59,096 --> 00:03:01,390
-Bit cold.
-Look at that view.

47
00:03:01,473 --> 00:03:04,768
DONNA: Yup, beautiful, cold view.

48
00:03:04,851 --> 00:03:08,355
Millions of planets, millions of
galaxies, and we're on this one.

49
00:03:08,438 --> 00:03:12,067
"Motto bene, bellissimo, " says Donna.

50
00:03:12,150 --> 00:03:13,819
Born in Chiswick.

51
00:03:13,902 --> 00:03:18,573
Oh, you've had a life of work and sleep,
telly and rent and tax,

52
00:03:18,657 --> 00:03:22,577
and takeaway dinners,
all birthdays and Christmases,

53
00:03:22,661 --> 00:03:26,540
and two weeks' holiday a year,
and then you end up here.

54
00:03:26,623 --> 00:03:30,961
Donna Noble, citizen of the Earth,
standing on a different planet.

55
00:03:31,461 --> 00:03:33,380
How about that, Donna?

56
00:03:34,715 --> 00:03:36,216
Donna?

57
00:03:37,509 --> 00:03:39,094
Sorry, you were saying?

58
00:03:39,177 --> 00:03:41,263
-Better?
-Lovely, thanks.

59
00:03:41,346 --> 00:03:42,973
-Comfy?
-Yup.

60
00:03:43,098 --> 00:03:44,975
Can you hear anything inside that?

61
00:03:45,100 --> 00:03:46,518
Pardon?

62
00:03:46,601 --> 00:03:49,646
Right, I was saying,
citizen of the Earth...

63
00:03:50,981 --> 00:03:52,566
A rocket!

64
00:03:52,649 --> 00:03:55,694
Blimey, a real proper rocket!

65
00:03:56,653 --> 00:03:58,822
Now, that's what I call a spaceship.

66
00:03:58,947 --> 00:04:01,575
You've got a box. He's got a Ferrari.

67
00:04:01,658 --> 00:04:04,286
Come on, let's see where he's going.

68
00:04:10,333 --> 00:04:12,669
Mr Halpen, sir, Dr Ryder,
new head of Ood Management.

69
00:04:12,794 --> 00:04:14,588
How many dead?
Come on, facts and figures.

70
00:04:14,671 --> 00:04:16,381
I haven't flown all this way
to discuss the weather,

71
00:04:16,506 --> 00:04:18,759
-which by the way, is freezing.
-Solana has the figures, sir.

72
00:04:18,842 --> 00:04:21,970
Solana Mercurio, sir,
head of marketing and galactic liaison.

73
00:04:22,053 --> 00:04:23,889
That's just what I need, a PR woman.

74
00:04:24,014 --> 00:04:26,141
I don't want a word of this getting out.
Is that understood?

75
00:04:26,224 --> 00:04:28,977
Now, get to the point. How many dead?

76
00:04:29,686 --> 00:04:32,939
In the past financial quarter,
we've had three deaths in the complex,

77
00:04:33,023 --> 00:04:36,151
all attributed to heart attacks
or industrial accidents.

78
00:04:36,234 --> 00:04:40,238
But now we've captured this on tape,
the cause would seem the same.

79
00:04:40,363 --> 00:04:43,116
He's using the translator ball
as a weapon. How does that work?

80
00:04:43,200 --> 00:04:46,036
I have no idea. I'm checking
the equipment. Nothing so far.

81
00:04:46,161 --> 00:04:49,623
-Can't see its eyes from this angle.
-I think we have to assume...

82
00:04:49,706 --> 00:04:51,458
-Red eye.
-I would think so, sir.

83
00:04:51,541 --> 00:04:54,669
-That Ood, what happened to it?
-It ran for the wild, sir, like a dog.

84
00:04:54,753 --> 00:04:58,048
One of the guards fired off a shot.
It'll be dead by now.

85
00:04:58,173 --> 00:04:59,841
Can I ask, what's red eye, sir?

86
00:04:59,925 --> 00:05:03,345
It's some sort of infection.
The Ood eyes literally change colour.

87
00:05:03,428 --> 00:05:05,388
-Drink.
-I can't find the source.

88
00:05:05,514 --> 00:05:07,557
All the bacterial scans
register negative.

89
00:05:07,641 --> 00:05:09,851
I'm sorry, but according to
your own rules, sir,

90
00:05:09,935 --> 00:05:12,229
there's no alcohol allowed on base.

91
00:05:12,312 --> 00:05:14,856
It's hair tonic if you must know.

92
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:20,654
Five years ago,
I had a full head of hair.

93
00:05:20,737 --> 00:05:23,406
Stress. That's what this is, stress.

94
00:05:28,078 --> 00:05:30,580
(BOTH LAUGHING)

95
00:05:35,210 --> 00:05:36,795
(MELODIC SINGING)

96
00:05:36,878 --> 00:05:39,089
Hold on. Can you hear that?

97
00:05:39,589 --> 00:05:42,050
Donna, take your hood down.

98
00:05:42,133 --> 00:05:43,552
What?

99
00:05:44,302 --> 00:05:46,680
That noise, it's like a song.

100
00:05:48,515 --> 00:05:49,975
Over there!

101
00:05:52,435 --> 00:05:56,273
-What is it?
-An Ood. He's called an Ood.

102
00:05:56,439 --> 00:05:58,233
But its face...

103
00:05:58,400 --> 00:06:02,362
Donna, don't, not now.
It's a he, not an it. Give me a hand.

104
00:06:02,445 --> 00:06:03,738
Sorry.

105
00:06:04,948 --> 00:06:08,118
I don't know where the heart is.
I don't know if he's got a heart.

106
00:06:08,243 --> 00:06:12,247
-Talk to him. Keep him going.
-It's all right. We've got you.

107
00:06:12,914 --> 00:06:15,458
Um, what's your name?

108
00:06:16,459 --> 00:06:19,880
Designated Ood Delta 50.

109
00:06:23,633 --> 00:06:26,803
-My name's Donna.
-No, no, no, no. You don't need to.

110
00:06:26,928 --> 00:06:28,179
Sorry.

111
00:06:29,472 --> 00:06:30,682
Oh, God.

112
00:06:30,765 --> 00:06:34,686
This is the Doctor.
Just what you need, a doctor.

113
00:06:35,145 --> 00:06:38,273
-Couldn't be better, eh?
-You've been shot.

114
00:06:38,440 --> 00:06:40,191
-The circle...
-No, don't try to talk.

115
00:06:40,275 --> 00:06:43,278
-The circle must be broken.
-Circle? What do you mean?

116
00:06:43,361 --> 00:06:46,656
Delta 50, what circle?
Delta 50, what circle?

117
00:06:46,990 --> 00:06:48,825
(ROARING)

118
00:06:50,827 --> 00:06:52,662
(GROANING)

119
00:06:56,875 --> 00:06:58,293
He's gone.

120
00:06:59,836 --> 00:07:01,171
Careful.

121
00:07:03,298 --> 00:07:05,508
There you are, sweetheart.

122
00:07:06,968 --> 00:07:10,347
We were too late.
What do we do? Do we bury him?

123
00:07:10,430 --> 00:07:12,599
The snow'll take care of that.

124
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:15,101
Who was he? What's an Ood?

125
00:07:15,185 --> 00:07:18,605
They're servants of humans
in the 42nd century.

126
00:07:19,522 --> 00:07:23,818
Mildly telepathic. That was their song.
It was his mind calling out.

127
00:07:24,694 --> 00:07:26,780
Couldn't hear anything.

128
00:07:29,115 --> 00:07:32,118
DONNA: He sang as he was dying.
DOCTOR: His eyes turned red.

129
00:07:32,202 --> 00:07:34,204
What's that mean?

130
00:07:34,287 --> 00:07:36,206
Trouble. Come on.

131
00:07:37,248 --> 00:07:39,376
DOCTOR: The Ood are harmless.
They're completely benign.

132
00:07:39,459 --> 00:07:41,878
Except the last time I met them,
there was this force,

133
00:07:42,003 --> 00:07:46,007
like a stronger mind,
powerful enough to take them over.

134
00:07:46,091 --> 00:07:48,927
-What sort of force?
-Ah, long story.

135
00:07:49,010 --> 00:07:51,429
-Long walk.
-It was the devil.

136
00:07:51,513 --> 00:07:54,224
If you're gonna take the mickey,
I'll just put my hood back up.

137
00:07:54,391 --> 00:07:56,559
Must be something different
this time, though,

138
00:07:56,685 --> 00:07:58,812
something closer to home.

139
00:07:59,688 --> 00:08:01,231
Aha!

140
00:08:01,314 --> 00:08:02,857
Civilisation!

141
00:08:05,527 --> 00:08:08,822
Ladies and gentlemen,
welcome to the Ood Sphere.

142
00:08:08,905 --> 00:08:10,532
And isn't it bracing?

143
00:08:10,657 --> 00:08:12,909
Here are your information packs,
with vouchers,

144
00:08:12,993 --> 00:08:15,954
3D tickets and a map of the complex.

145
00:08:16,079 --> 00:08:18,039
My name's Solana, head of marketing.

146
00:08:18,123 --> 00:08:20,000
I'm sure we've all spoken
on the vid-phone.

147
00:08:20,083 --> 00:08:21,334
If you'd like to follow me...

148
00:08:21,418 --> 00:08:24,337
Sorry! Late. Don't mind us.
Hello. The guards let us through.

149
00:08:24,462 --> 00:08:26,840
-And you would be?
-The Doctor and Donna Noble.

150
00:08:26,923 --> 00:08:31,511
Representing the Noble Corporation,
PLC Limited, Intergalactic.

151
00:08:31,594 --> 00:08:34,556
Must have fallen off my list.
My apologies. Won't happen again.

152
00:08:34,639 --> 00:08:37,100
Now then, Dr Noble, Mrs Noble,
if you'd like to come with me?

153
00:08:37,183 --> 00:08:39,436
-Oh, no, no, no, we're not married.
-We're so not married.

154
00:08:39,519 --> 00:08:40,770
-No.
-Never, ever.

155
00:08:40,854 --> 00:08:44,566
Of course. And here are your
information packs, vouchers inside.

156
00:08:44,649 --> 00:08:48,028
Now, if you'd like to come with me,
the executive suites are nice and warm.

157
00:08:48,111 --> 00:08:49,362
(ALARM BLARING)

158
00:08:49,446 --> 00:08:51,448
Oh, what's that?
That sounds like an alarm.

159
00:08:51,948 --> 00:08:53,825
For God's sake,
we've got the buyers arriving.

160
00:08:53,908 --> 00:08:56,077
Who sounded the alarm? Drink.

161
00:08:56,161 --> 00:08:58,663
Oh, it's just a siren
for the end of the work shift.

162
00:08:58,747 --> 00:09:01,458
Now then, this way, quick as you can.

163
00:09:03,126 --> 00:09:05,754
-Mr Kess, what the hell is going on?
-Ood on the loose, sir.

164
00:09:05,837 --> 00:09:08,006
-Looks like we got another one.
-Red eye?

165
00:09:08,131 --> 00:09:10,884
As red as sin, sir.
Don't worry, Mr Halpen. We're on it.

166
00:09:10,967 --> 00:09:13,470
-Sir! -A I - LL right, guys

167
00:09:13,553 --> 00:09:14,888
Go! Get him!

168
00:09:15,013 --> 00:09:17,849
As you can see,
the Ood are happy to serve,

169
00:09:17,974 --> 00:09:20,810
and we keep them in facilities
of the highest standard.

170
00:09:22,437 --> 00:09:25,565
Here at the Double-O,
that's Ood Operations,

171
00:09:25,648 --> 00:09:28,610
we like to think of the Ood
as our trusted friends.

172
00:09:28,693 --> 00:09:30,779
You two, go left! You two, follow me!

173
00:09:30,862 --> 00:09:33,615
We keep the Ood healthy,
safe and educated.

174
00:09:33,782 --> 00:09:36,659
-Come on!
-Take him alive!

175
00:09:37,494 --> 00:09:41,289
We don't just breed the Ood,
we make them better.

176
00:09:42,832 --> 00:09:47,670
Because at heart, what is an Ood
but a reflection of us?

177
00:09:48,880 --> 00:09:50,840
If your Ood is happy...

178
00:09:51,132 --> 00:09:53,343
(ROARING)

179
00:09:54,302 --> 00:09:56,638
...then you'll be happy, too.

180
00:09:59,015 --> 00:10:02,519
Mr Halpen, this is a bit more
than red eye, sir.

181
00:10:04,187 --> 00:10:07,524
This is something new. It's rabid, sir.

182
00:10:07,649 --> 00:10:09,025
(ROARING)

183
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:13,154
Take it to Dr Ryder.
Just get it out of sight.

184
00:10:14,781 --> 00:10:17,492
MAN ON INTERCOM:
Sales speakers needed by 71900, sir.

185
00:10:17,575 --> 00:10:19,327
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

186
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:30,380
What do you think? Growing back?
Just a little bit?

187
00:10:33,383 --> 00:10:34,884
Like you'd know.

188
00:10:35,510 --> 00:10:39,430
I'd now like to point out a new
innovation from Ood Operations.

189
00:10:39,556 --> 00:10:43,143
We've introduced a variety package
with the Ood translator ball.

190
00:10:43,226 --> 00:10:45,436
You can now have the standard setting.

191
00:10:45,520 --> 00:10:47,438
How are you today, Ood?

192
00:10:47,564 --> 00:10:49,482
I'm perfectly well, thank you.

193
00:10:49,566 --> 00:10:53,236
Or perhaps after a stressful day,
a little something for the gentlemen.

194
00:10:53,319 --> 00:10:54,988
And how are you, Ood?

195
00:10:55,071 --> 00:10:57,365
IN FEMALE VOICE:
All the better for seeing you.

196
00:10:57,448 --> 00:11:00,702
And the comedy classic option.
Ood, you dropped something.

197
00:11:00,785 --> 00:11:02,328
D'oh!

198
00:11:02,954 --> 00:11:05,707
All that for only
five additional credits.

199
00:11:05,832 --> 00:11:07,792
The details are in your brochures.

200
00:11:07,917 --> 00:11:11,880
Now, there's plenty more food and drink,
so don't hold back.

201
00:11:20,471 --> 00:11:21,931
Ah, got it.

202
00:11:22,640 --> 00:11:27,020
The Ood Sphere. I've been to this
solar system before, years ago.

203
00:11:27,103 --> 00:11:30,565
Ages. Close to the planet Sense Sphere.

204
00:11:30,648 --> 00:11:32,609
Let's widen it out.

205
00:11:36,112 --> 00:11:38,114
The year 4126.

206
00:11:38,198 --> 00:11:42,202
That is the Second Great
and Bountiful Human Empire.

207
00:11:42,285 --> 00:11:44,454
41267

208
00:11:45,079 --> 00:11:50,543
It's 4126? I'm in 4126.

209
00:11:50,877 --> 00:11:52,128
It's good, isn't it?

210
00:11:52,212 --> 00:11:53,922
What's the Earth like now?

211
00:11:54,005 --> 00:11:57,884
A bit full, but the empire
stretches out across three galaxies.

212
00:11:57,967 --> 00:12:02,805
It's weird. I mean, it's brilliant,
but back home, the papers and telly,

213
00:12:02,889 --> 00:12:04,974
they keep saying
we haven't got long to live.

214
00:12:05,058 --> 00:12:08,937
Global warming, flooding,
all the bees disappearing.

215
00:12:09,020 --> 00:12:12,774
Yeah, that thing about the bees is odd.

216
00:12:13,358 --> 00:12:16,819
But look at us. We're everywhere.
Is that good or bad, though?

217
00:12:16,903 --> 00:12:20,073
Are we like explorers,
or more like a virus?

218
00:12:20,156 --> 00:12:21,824
Sometimes I wonder.

219
00:12:21,950 --> 00:12:25,286
-What are the red dots?
-Ood distribution centres.

220
00:12:25,370 --> 00:12:29,040
Across three galaxies?
Don't the Ood get a say in this?

221
00:12:31,376 --> 00:12:34,712
Um, sorry, but...

222
00:12:38,341 --> 00:12:39,592
Hello.

223
00:12:39,676 --> 00:12:42,136
Tell me, are you all like this?

224
00:12:42,512 --> 00:12:44,097
I do not understand, miss.

225
00:12:44,180 --> 00:12:47,767
-Why'd you say "miss"? Do I look single?
-Back to the point.

226
00:12:47,850 --> 00:12:52,230
Yeah. What I mean is,
are there any free Ood?

227
00:12:52,355 --> 00:12:56,651
Are there Ood running wild somewhere,
like wildebeest?

228
00:12:56,734 --> 00:13:00,321
All Ood are born to serve.
Otherwise we would die.

229
00:13:00,405 --> 00:13:03,074
You can't have started like that.

230
00:13:03,157 --> 00:13:06,119
Before the humans, what were you like?

231
00:13:06,202 --> 00:13:09,038
-The circle.
-What do you mean? What circle?

232
00:13:09,163 --> 00:13:11,291
The... The circle is...

233
00:13:11,374 --> 00:13:15,169
Ladies and gentlemen,
all Ood to hospitality stations, please.

234
00:13:15,295 --> 00:13:17,880
I've had enough of this schmoozing.

235
00:13:17,964 --> 00:13:20,008
Do you fancy getting off
the beaten track?

236
00:13:20,091 --> 00:13:21,718
SOLANA: If I can introduce you...

237
00:13:21,801 --> 00:13:24,220
"Rough Guide to the Ood Sphere"?
Works for me.

238
00:13:24,304 --> 00:13:25,388
Yeah.

239
00:13:25,930 --> 00:13:27,265
(ROARING)

240
00:13:27,598 --> 00:13:28,891
What the hell is wrong with it?

241
00:13:29,017 --> 00:13:32,520
It's obviously stage two of red eye,
whatever that means.

242
00:13:32,603 --> 00:13:35,440
Ood Sigma, have you seen this before?

243
00:13:35,565 --> 00:13:38,484
Humanity defines us, sir.
We look to you for answers.

244
00:13:38,568 --> 00:13:41,070
Oh, fat lot of good, all of you.

245
00:13:42,530 --> 00:13:46,117
We're exporting hundreds of thousands
of Ood to all the civilised planets.

246
00:13:46,242 --> 00:13:48,453
If they turn rabid,
you know what it'll mean.

247
00:13:48,578 --> 00:13:52,582
There's only one thing
I haven't checked, sir. Warehouse 15.

248
00:13:52,665 --> 00:13:54,834
Why should that cause trouble?
It's been two centuries now.

249
00:13:54,917 --> 00:13:58,171
-No change. Not ever. Drink.
-I know it's restricted access,

250
00:13:58,254 --> 00:14:02,091
but if I'm going to work on this,
I should see it, just in case.

251
00:14:02,216 --> 00:14:04,177
Can't stand the place.

252
00:14:06,137 --> 00:14:08,222
Let's go. Warehouse 15, then. Come on.

253
00:14:08,306 --> 00:14:10,433
What about this one, sir?

254
00:14:12,477 --> 00:14:16,564
I would suggest a postmortem,
which means it's gotta be dead first.

255
00:14:21,277 --> 00:14:22,528
(GUNS COCKING)

256
00:14:22,612 --> 00:14:24,113
(GUNS FIRING)

257
00:14:52,392 --> 00:14:53,768
Get up.

258
00:14:53,851 --> 00:14:55,561
I said, get up.

259
00:14:55,645 --> 00:14:56,979
Servants?

260
00:14:57,563 --> 00:14:58,856
They're slaves.

261
00:14:58,940 --> 00:15:00,191
Get up!

262
00:15:01,651 --> 00:15:02,902
March.

263
00:15:03,319 --> 00:15:07,031
Last time I met the Ood,
I never thought, never asked.

264
00:15:07,115 --> 00:15:09,784
-That's not like you.
-I was busy.

265
00:15:10,326 --> 00:15:13,538
So busy I couldn't save them.
I had to let the Ood die.

266
00:15:13,621 --> 00:15:15,665
I reckon I owe them one.

267
00:15:16,040 --> 00:15:18,334
That looks like the boss.

268
00:15:18,418 --> 00:15:21,003
Let's keep out of his way. Come on.

269
00:15:23,798 --> 00:15:26,509
How long since you went inside?

270
00:15:26,592 --> 00:15:28,970
Must be 10 years ago.

271
00:15:32,765 --> 00:15:34,350
COMPUTER VOICE: Warehouse 15.

272
00:15:34,434 --> 00:15:36,894
My father brought me here
when I was six years old.

273
00:15:37,019 --> 00:15:38,729
Security protocol initiated.

274
00:15:38,813 --> 00:15:42,316
-God, the stench of it.
-Warehouse 15 door open.

275
00:15:57,165 --> 00:15:58,791
Incredible.

276
00:15:58,875 --> 00:16:01,919
Like I said, nothing's changed.

277
00:16:05,673 --> 00:16:10,136
I've read the documents,
but it doesn't quite prepare you.

278
00:16:10,595 --> 00:16:14,348
Is it just me or does it feel as if
it's looking at you?

279
00:16:14,432 --> 00:16:17,351
I think I understand
the barrier mechanics well enough.

280
00:16:17,435 --> 00:16:19,187
Check the signal.

281
00:16:21,355 --> 00:16:23,941
I suppose it's home, sweet home to you.

282
00:16:24,025 --> 00:16:27,069
-What do you think?
-I have no opinion, sir.

283
00:16:27,153 --> 00:16:31,657
Well, say hello to Daddy.

284
00:16:32,658 --> 00:16:35,578
Nothing. The barrier's intact.
No abnormal signal.

285
00:16:35,661 --> 00:16:38,122
Same as it's been for 200 years.

286
00:16:39,373 --> 00:16:42,210
SOLANA: Mr Halpen, the two people from
the Noble Corporation

287
00:16:42,293 --> 00:16:44,128
failed to pass security checks.

288
00:16:44,212 --> 00:16:48,299
There's no such company.
The Noble Corporation doesn't exist.

289
00:16:48,382 --> 00:16:50,843
And on top of that,
they seem to have gone missing, sir,

290
00:16:50,927 --> 00:16:52,929
the Doctor and Miss Noble.

291
00:16:53,012 --> 00:16:54,472
Just what I need.

292
00:16:54,597 --> 00:16:58,017
Start a search. No alarms, got that?
Keep it quiet.

293
00:17:00,686 --> 00:17:03,439
You see? Hair loss. Drink.

294
00:17:06,651 --> 00:17:08,819
Tell you what, old friend.

295
00:17:10,029 --> 00:17:12,198
Have this one on me.

296
00:17:12,281 --> 00:17:13,574
Cheers.

297
00:17:14,158 --> 00:17:15,910
(ROARING)

298
00:17:17,912 --> 00:17:20,081
I think we're finished here.

299
00:17:26,170 --> 00:17:27,630
Sorry.

300
00:17:41,352 --> 00:17:45,147
-Where'd you learn to whistle?
-West Ham, every Saturday.

301
00:18:03,583 --> 00:18:05,042
DOCTOR: Ood export.

302
00:18:05,668 --> 00:18:07,211
You see?

303
00:18:07,295 --> 00:18:11,215
Lifts up the containers,
takes them to the rocket ships,

304
00:18:11,299 --> 00:18:14,760
ready to be flown out
all over the three galaxies.

305
00:18:15,553 --> 00:18:18,639
What, you mean these containers
are full of...

306
00:18:18,723 --> 00:18:20,516
What do you think?

307
00:18:28,024 --> 00:18:30,526
Oh, it stinks.

308
00:18:32,862 --> 00:18:35,823
How many of them do you think
there are in each one?

309
00:18:35,906 --> 00:18:37,491
A hundred. More.

310
00:18:37,867 --> 00:18:41,037
A great, big empire built on slavery.

311
00:18:41,203 --> 00:18:43,205
It's not so different from your time.

312
00:18:43,289 --> 00:18:45,291
Oi, I haven't got slaves.

313
00:18:45,374 --> 00:18:47,501
Who do you think made your clothes?

314
00:18:48,336 --> 00:18:51,297
Is that why you travel around
with a human at your side?

315
00:18:51,380 --> 00:18:54,175
It's not so you can show them
the wonders of the universe.

316
00:18:54,258 --> 00:18:57,762
-It's so you can take cheap shots.
-Sorry.

317
00:18:57,845 --> 00:18:59,096
Don't.

318
00:19:00,139 --> 00:19:01,557
Spaceman.

319
00:19:02,808 --> 00:19:04,060
I don't understand,

320
00:19:04,143 --> 00:19:06,437
the door was open,
why don't you just run away?

321
00:19:06,562 --> 00:19:09,482
-For what reason?
-You could be free.

322
00:19:09,565 --> 00:19:12,068
I do not understand the concept.

323
00:19:12,902 --> 00:19:15,112
What is it with that Persil ball?

324
00:19:15,196 --> 00:19:17,406
I mean, they're not born with it,
are they?

325
00:19:17,490 --> 00:19:19,408
Why do they have to be all plugged in?

326
00:19:19,533 --> 00:19:22,745
Ood, tell me, does the circle
mean anything to you?

327
00:19:22,870 --> 00:19:24,997
ALL: 7he circle must be broken.

328
00:19:26,082 --> 00:19:28,084
Oh, that is creepy.

329
00:19:28,834 --> 00:19:32,630
-What is it? What is the circle?
-ALL: The circle must be broken.

330
00:19:32,755 --> 00:19:34,256
Why?

331
00:19:34,340 --> 00:19:36,217
So that we can sing.

332
00:19:37,259 --> 00:19:39,512
Mr Halpen, I'm in Ood Cargo.

333
00:19:39,595 --> 00:19:41,889
I've found your unwanted guests.

334
00:19:41,972 --> 00:19:43,099
Go!

335
00:19:43,432 --> 00:19:44,892
(ALARM BLARING)

336
00:19:44,975 --> 00:19:46,477
That's us. Come on.

337
00:19:46,602 --> 00:19:50,356
Cut the alarms! I said, no alarms!

338
00:19:51,023 --> 00:19:53,317
Nothing to worry about,
ladies and gentlemen.

339
00:19:53,401 --> 00:19:57,530
It's just a fire drill. We test
the system at this time every day.

340
00:19:57,613 --> 00:19:59,365
If you'll excuse me...

341
00:20:06,330 --> 00:20:08,416
Doctor! There's a door!

342
00:20:09,709 --> 00:20:11,836
GUARD: Don't move!

343
00:20:11,961 --> 00:20:13,379
-Where've you gone?
-GUARD: Stay where you are!

344
00:20:13,462 --> 00:20:15,589
-Help me!
-Keep her here for now.

345
00:20:15,673 --> 00:20:18,467
Help me! Get off me!

346
00:20:25,474 --> 00:20:27,476
Donna, where are you?

347
00:20:30,229 --> 00:20:31,981
-All guards withdraw.
-Sir?

348
00:20:32,064 --> 00:20:35,443
I said, withdraw. Keep to the perimeter.

349
00:20:35,526 --> 00:20:37,319
I've got this one.

350
00:20:42,324 --> 00:20:44,785
I've always wanted to do this.

351
00:20:44,869 --> 00:20:46,245
(GRUNTING)

352
00:20:51,208 --> 00:20:53,085
Container locked.

353
00:20:53,169 --> 00:20:54,378
Ahhh!

354
00:21:07,767 --> 00:21:09,477
Can you help me?

355
00:21:10,686 --> 00:21:12,396
Oh, no, you don't.

356
00:21:25,034 --> 00:21:27,453
What have I done?
I'm not one of that lot.

357
00:21:27,536 --> 00:21:29,288
I'm on your side.

358
00:21:39,882 --> 00:21:42,301
Stay where you are. That's an order.

359
00:21:42,384 --> 00:21:44,053
I said, stay.

360
00:21:44,136 --> 00:21:46,388
Doctor! Doctor!

361
00:22:00,986 --> 00:22:02,863
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

362
00:22:07,409 --> 00:22:10,579
You heard the instructions.
Mr Halpen wants them alive.

363
00:22:10,704 --> 00:22:12,832
Doctor, get me out!

364
00:22:13,123 --> 00:22:16,168
Doctor, get me out of here!

365
00:22:16,252 --> 00:22:18,671
If you don't do what she says,
you're really in trouble.

366
00:22:18,754 --> 00:22:21,966
-Not from me, from her.
-Unlock the container.

367
00:22:24,760 --> 00:22:26,053
Doctor.

368
00:22:26,512 --> 00:22:29,306
There we go. Safe and sound.

369
00:22:29,431 --> 00:22:31,809
Never mind about me. What about them?

370
00:22:33,185 --> 00:22:34,979
To the left! Fire!

371
00:22:37,940 --> 00:22:39,525
Shoot to kill!

372
00:22:59,503 --> 00:23:02,131
If people back on Earth knew
what was going on here...

373
00:23:02,214 --> 00:23:04,383
Don't be so stupid. Of course they know.

374
00:23:04,466 --> 00:23:08,304
-They know how you treat the Ood?
-They don't ask. Same thing.

375
00:23:08,429 --> 00:23:10,556
Solana, the Ood aren't born like this.
They can't be.

376
00:23:10,639 --> 00:23:12,766
A species born to serve
could never evolve in the first place.

377
00:23:12,850 --> 00:23:14,560
What does the company do
to make them obey?

378
00:23:14,643 --> 00:23:17,146
-It's nothing to do with me.
-Oh, what, 'cause you don't ask?

379
00:23:17,271 --> 00:23:21,692
-That's Dr Ryder's territory.
-Where is he? What part of the complex?

380
00:23:23,027 --> 00:23:25,321
I could help with the red eye.
Now, show me!

381
00:23:25,446 --> 00:23:27,781
There, beyond the red section.

382
00:23:27,907 --> 00:23:29,325
Come with me.

383
00:23:29,408 --> 00:23:31,535
You've seen the warehouse.
You can't agree with all this.

384
00:23:31,619 --> 00:23:35,039
You know this place better than me.
You could help.

385
00:23:39,376 --> 00:23:43,130
They're over here!
Guards! They're over here!

386
00:23:43,881 --> 00:23:47,509
Male and female suspects escaped.
West ridge corridor.

387
00:23:54,350 --> 00:23:57,603
Mr Halpen, I found the Doctor.
He's heading for Ood Conversion.

388
00:23:57,686 --> 00:23:58,771
On my way.

389
00:23:59,188 --> 00:24:00,898
Mr Kess, what's the situation?

390
00:24:01,065 --> 00:24:03,150
We've contained it, sir. Fenced them in.

391
00:24:03,233 --> 00:24:06,236
But the red eye seems to be
permanent this time. It's not fading.

392
00:24:06,362 --> 00:24:09,740
Worse than that, sir,
there's more of them going rabid.

393
00:24:10,449 --> 00:24:12,326
In my opinion, sir,
I think we've lost them.

394
00:24:12,409 --> 00:24:14,286
The entire batch contaminated.

395
00:24:14,370 --> 00:24:16,538
What's causing it? Why now?

396
00:24:17,206 --> 00:24:19,208
What's changed?

397
00:24:25,089 --> 00:24:27,883
-How many Ood in total?
-I'd say about 2,000, sir.

398
00:24:27,967 --> 00:24:30,511
We can write them off.
That's what insurance is for.

399
00:24:30,594 --> 00:24:32,054
Drink.

400
00:24:32,137 --> 00:24:36,016
We've plenty more on the breeding farms.
Let's start again.

401
00:24:41,271 --> 00:24:43,691
Fetch the canisters. No survivors.

402
00:24:43,774 --> 00:24:45,150
My pleasure, sir.

403
00:24:45,234 --> 00:24:47,069
You lot, canisters.

404
00:24:48,612 --> 00:24:50,030
This way!

405
00:24:59,915 --> 00:25:01,917
Oh, can you hear it?

406
00:25:02,001 --> 00:25:04,336
I didn't need the map.
I should have listened.

407
00:25:11,802 --> 00:25:14,638
-Does that mean we're locked in?
-Listen.

408
00:25:15,431 --> 00:25:17,766
Listen, listen, listen, listen.

409
00:25:17,933 --> 00:25:19,935
(MELODIC SINGING)

410
00:25:28,110 --> 00:25:29,611
Oh, my head.

411
00:25:30,320 --> 00:25:32,031
What is it?

412
00:25:32,114 --> 00:25:34,992
Can't you hear it? The singing.

413
00:25:56,305 --> 00:25:58,891
DONNA: They look different
to the others.

414
00:25:59,767 --> 00:26:02,436
That's because they're natural-born Ood,
unprocessed,

415
00:26:02,519 --> 00:26:05,814
before they're adapted to slavery,
unspoiled.

416
00:26:10,277 --> 00:26:12,071
That's their song.

417
00:26:13,030 --> 00:26:15,032
I can't hear it.

418
00:26:15,157 --> 00:26:16,992
Do you want to?

419
00:26:19,161 --> 00:26:20,329
Yeah.

420
00:26:21,080 --> 00:26:23,290
It's the song of captivity.

421
00:26:23,999 --> 00:26:26,668
-Let me hear it.
-Face me.

422
00:26:32,925 --> 00:26:36,220
Open your mind, that's it.
Hear it, Donna.

423
00:26:36,345 --> 00:26:38,180
(MELODIC SINGING)

424
00:26:38,806 --> 00:26:40,390
Hear the music.

425
00:26:57,825 --> 00:26:59,368
Take it away.

426
00:27:00,702 --> 00:27:02,037
You sure?

427
00:27:02,162 --> 00:27:04,206
I can't bear it.

428
00:27:08,794 --> 00:27:10,170
I'm sorry.

429
00:27:10,295 --> 00:27:11,630
It's okay.

430
00:27:16,593 --> 00:27:18,762
But you can still hear it?

431
00:27:21,181 --> 00:27:22,933
All the time.

432
00:27:28,397 --> 00:27:29,898
Come on, what's the hold-up?

433
00:27:30,023 --> 00:27:33,152
It's the experimentation lab.
Maximum security. He's fused the system.

434
00:27:33,235 --> 00:27:36,321
Well, don't just stand there!
Get the boltcutters. Rip that door off!

435
00:27:36,405 --> 00:27:37,781
Solana, go back to the reps.

436
00:27:37,865 --> 00:27:39,992
I don't want any of them wandering off
and seeing this.

437
00:27:40,075 --> 00:27:43,162
And get them away from the Ood,
just in case.

438
00:27:43,245 --> 00:27:44,580
-Hurry up!
-Yes, sir.

439
00:27:47,833 --> 00:27:49,751
(METAL CLANGING)

440
00:27:49,835 --> 00:27:52,588
-They're breaking in.
-Ah, let them.

441
00:27:54,756 --> 00:27:57,092
What are you holding? Show me.

442
00:28:00,012 --> 00:28:01,263
Friend.

443
00:28:02,514 --> 00:28:05,017
Doctor, Donna. Friend.

444
00:28:05,100 --> 00:28:06,685
Let me see.

445
00:28:06,768 --> 00:28:08,478
Look at me.

446
00:28:08,604 --> 00:28:11,231
Let me see. That's it.

447
00:28:11,356 --> 00:28:13,442
That's good. Go on.

448
00:28:20,490 --> 00:28:21,950
Is that...

449
00:28:22,451 --> 00:28:27,164
It's a brain. A hindbrain.
The Ood are born with a secondary brain.

450
00:28:27,289 --> 00:28:30,000
Like the amygdala in humans,
it processes memory and emotions.

451
00:28:30,125 --> 00:28:31,960
You get rid of that,
you wouldn't be Donna any more.

452
00:28:32,085 --> 00:28:34,296
You'd be like an Ood, a processed Ood.

453
00:28:34,379 --> 00:28:38,008
So the company cuts off their brains.

454
00:28:38,091 --> 00:28:40,510
And they stitch on the translator.

455
00:28:40,594 --> 00:28:42,262
Like a lobotomy.

456
00:28:43,305 --> 00:28:45,974
I spent all that time
looking for you, Doctor.

457
00:28:46,058 --> 00:28:49,311
I guess I thought
it was so wonderful out here.

458
00:28:52,147 --> 00:28:53,941
I want to go home.

459
00:28:56,902 --> 00:28:58,153
(DOOR OPENING)

460
00:28:58,237 --> 00:29:00,656
They're with the Ood, sir.

461
00:29:00,739 --> 00:29:03,367
What are you gonna do, then? Arrest me?

462
00:29:03,492 --> 00:29:05,452
Lock me up? Throw me in a cage?

463
00:29:05,535 --> 00:29:07,996
Well, you're too late. Ha!

464
00:29:09,248 --> 00:29:12,042
Why don't you just come out and say it?
Photo activists.

465
00:29:12,167 --> 00:29:14,253
If that's what Friends of the Ood
are trying to prove, then yes.

466
00:29:14,336 --> 00:29:18,173
The Ood were nothing without us,
just animals roaming around on the ice.

467
00:29:18,257 --> 00:29:20,050
That's because you can't hear them.

468
00:29:20,175 --> 00:29:22,844
They welcomed it.
It's not as if they put up a fight.

469
00:29:22,928 --> 00:29:24,680
You idiot.

470
00:29:24,763 --> 00:29:27,516
They're born with their brains
in their hands.

471
00:29:27,599 --> 00:29:30,519
Don't you see? That makes them peaceful.

472
00:29:30,602 --> 00:29:32,187
They've got to be
because a creature like that

473
00:29:32,312 --> 00:29:33,772
would have to trust anyone it meets.

474
00:29:33,855 --> 00:29:35,816
-Oh, nice one.
-Thank you.

475
00:29:35,899 --> 00:29:40,279
The system's worked for 200 years.
All we've got is a rogue batch.

476
00:29:40,362 --> 00:29:43,448
But the infection is
about to be sterilised.

477
00:29:44,783 --> 00:29:46,451
Mr Kess, how do we stand?

478
00:29:47,286 --> 00:29:49,288
Canisters primed, sir.

479
00:29:49,371 --> 00:29:53,083
As soon as the core heats up,
the gas is released.

480
00:29:53,208 --> 00:29:56,545
Give it 200 marks and counting.

481
00:29:56,920 --> 00:29:59,965
-You're gonna gas them?
-Kill the livestock.

482
00:30:00,048 --> 00:30:03,302
The classic foot-and-mouth solution
from the olden days.

483
00:30:03,385 --> 00:30:05,053
Still works.

484
00:30:08,223 --> 00:30:10,892
(OOD SINGING)

485
00:30:20,986 --> 00:30:23,071
I'm sorry, if I could ask you
one more time,

486
00:30:23,155 --> 00:30:26,033
could all the reps please come through
to the education suites?

487
00:30:26,116 --> 00:30:29,619
Why move now? It's a free bar!

488
00:30:29,703 --> 00:30:33,415
Could I ask all the Ood to withdraw?
It's feeding time.

489
00:30:33,790 --> 00:30:37,836
Oh, you've upset them! Leave them alone.

490
00:30:37,961 --> 00:30:41,590
I have to insist,
if all the Ood could please leave...

491
00:30:52,642 --> 00:30:56,438
Ladies and gentlemen, change of plan.
If you could leave by the fire exits.

492
00:30:58,732 --> 00:31:01,610
I could sell this.
You could offer different colours.

493
00:31:09,659 --> 00:31:12,120
(TRANSLATOR BALLS BUZZING)

494
00:31:19,127 --> 00:31:22,130
They've gone insane, miss.
They've gone mad, all of them.

495
00:31:22,214 --> 00:31:24,633
Just shoot them! Shoot to kill!

496
00:31:38,063 --> 00:31:39,314
(ALARM BLARING)

497
00:31:39,439 --> 00:31:40,649
What the hell?

498
00:31:43,819 --> 00:31:45,987
What's going on out there?

499
00:31:50,867 --> 00:31:54,830
MAN: We have now Emergency status.
Emergency status.

500
00:31:55,580 --> 00:32:00,752
All exits sealed.
Emergency clearance authorised.

501
00:32:00,836 --> 00:32:03,839
Ood distribution centre
now completely...

502
00:32:08,552 --> 00:32:10,345
It's a revolution.

503
00:32:21,440 --> 00:32:24,317
Come back! Let me out of here!

504
00:32:27,028 --> 00:32:28,363
No!

505
00:32:28,488 --> 00:32:30,991
(SCREAMING)

506
00:32:33,160 --> 00:32:34,870
Change of plan.

507
00:32:34,995 --> 00:32:38,582
No reports of trouble off-world, sir.
It's still contained to the Ood Sphere.

508
00:32:38,665 --> 00:32:41,293
Then we've got a public duty
to stop it before it spreads.

509
00:32:41,376 --> 00:32:44,004
-What's happening?
-Everything you wanted, Doctor.

510
00:32:44,087 --> 00:32:46,131
No doubt there'll be
a full police investigation

511
00:32:46,214 --> 00:32:50,302
once this place has been sterilised,
so I can't risk a bullet to the head.

512
00:32:50,385 --> 00:32:52,137
I'll leave you
to the mercies of the Ood.

513
00:32:52,220 --> 00:32:55,140
Mr Halpen, there's something else,
isn't there? Something we haven't seen.

514
00:32:55,223 --> 00:32:56,266
What do you mean?

515
00:32:56,391 --> 00:32:58,602
A creature couldn't survive with
a separate forebrain and hindbrain.

516
00:32:58,727 --> 00:32:59,978
They'd be at war with themselves.

517
00:33:00,061 --> 00:33:02,105
There's got to be something else.
A third element, right?

518
00:33:02,230 --> 00:33:03,398
And again, so clever.

519
00:33:03,523 --> 00:33:06,985
It's got to be connected
to the red eye. What is it?

520
00:33:07,110 --> 00:33:09,738
It won't exist for very much longer.

521
00:33:10,906 --> 00:33:12,532
Enjoy your Ood.

522
00:33:18,205 --> 00:33:19,539
Come on.

523
00:33:20,415 --> 00:33:22,209
(MACHINE GUNS FIRING)

524
00:33:24,211 --> 00:33:27,214
-Dr Ryder, Warehouse 15.
-But what about this one?

525
00:33:27,297 --> 00:33:31,426
No. You've not turned.
Faithful to the last.

526
00:33:33,553 --> 00:33:36,515
Go, join your people
while you still can.

527
00:33:43,605 --> 00:33:44,940
Come on.

528
00:33:50,445 --> 00:33:54,115
Well, do something.
You're the one with all the tricks.

529
00:33:54,199 --> 00:33:58,370
-You must have met Houdini.
-These are really good handcuffs.

530
00:33:58,453 --> 00:34:02,541
Well, I'm glad of that.
I mean, at least we've got quality.

531
00:34:02,624 --> 00:34:04,459
(DOOR OPENING)

532
00:34:19,766 --> 00:34:22,394
-Uh, Doctor, Donna. Friends.
-The circle must be broken.

533
00:34:22,477 --> 00:34:24,104
-Doctor, Donna. Friends!
-The circle must be broken!

534
00:34:24,187 --> 00:34:26,565
-Doctor, Donna. Friends! Friends!
-The circle must be broken.

535
00:34:26,648 --> 00:34:29,442
-The circle must be broken!
-Doctor, Donna. Friends! Doctor...

536
00:34:29,526 --> 00:34:32,279
DONNA: (ECHOING)
The circle must be broken!

537
00:34:32,362 --> 00:34:35,240
-Doctor, Donna. Friends. Friends!
-The circle must be broken.

538
00:34:35,323 --> 00:34:36,992
-Doctor, Donna. Friends!
-The circle...

539
00:34:37,075 --> 00:34:38,994
DONNA: (ECHOING)
The circle must be broken!

540
00:34:39,119 --> 00:34:41,830
-Doctor, Donna. Friends!
-The circle must be broken!

541
00:34:41,913 --> 00:34:43,665
The circle must...

542
00:34:53,341 --> 00:34:55,385
(OOD SINGING)

543
00:35:00,140 --> 00:35:03,018
Doctor, Donna. Friends.

544
00:35:03,518 --> 00:35:05,520
-Yes! That's us! Friends! Oh, yes!
-That's him. That's me!

545
00:35:09,232 --> 00:35:11,276
(GUARD SCREAMING)

546
00:35:11,359 --> 00:35:13,695
No, leave him! Leave him.

547
00:35:17,490 --> 00:35:19,534
Behind you! Behind you!

548
00:35:21,161 --> 00:35:22,704
-I don't know where it is.
-GUARD: Fall back!

549
00:35:22,829 --> 00:35:27,292
-I don't know where they've gone.
-What are we looking for?

550
00:35:27,375 --> 00:35:31,463
It might be underground,
like some sort of cave or a cavern or...

551
00:35:32,672 --> 00:35:34,883
(MACHINE GUN FIRE CONTINUES)

552
00:35:39,888 --> 00:35:42,724
Warehouse 15, door open.

553
00:35:52,233 --> 00:35:53,902
All right?

554
00:35:59,824 --> 00:36:03,828
It's always been an option.
My grandfather drew up this plan.

555
00:36:03,912 --> 00:36:06,748
That's the advantage of
a family-run business, Dr Ryder.

556
00:36:06,873 --> 00:36:08,249
The personal touch.

557
00:36:08,333 --> 00:36:10,251
But we should evacuate.
If we can get to the rocket shed...

558
00:36:10,335 --> 00:36:12,921
No need. We've got this.

559
00:36:16,174 --> 00:36:17,926
Detonation packs.

560
00:36:18,843 --> 00:36:21,513
Place them around the circumference.

561
00:36:23,014 --> 00:36:25,433
We're going to blow it up.

562
00:36:25,558 --> 00:36:28,937
If this thing dies, so do the Ood.

563
00:36:56,798 --> 00:36:58,550
(MELODIC SINGING)

564
00:36:59,384 --> 00:37:00,969
The Ood brain.

565
00:37:01,970 --> 00:37:05,056
DOCTOR: Now it all makes sense.
That's the missing link.

566
00:37:05,140 --> 00:37:08,351
The third element binding them together.

567
00:37:08,435 --> 00:37:10,812
Forebrain, hindbrain and this.

568
00:37:11,771 --> 00:37:15,358
The telepathic centre.
It's a shared mind.

569
00:37:16,818 --> 00:37:19,154
Connecting all the Ood in song.

570
00:37:19,237 --> 00:37:20,405
(CHAINS RATTLING)

571
00:37:21,448 --> 00:37:24,242
Cargo. I could always go in to cargo.

572
00:37:24,868 --> 00:37:27,579
I've got the rockets,
I've got the sheds.

573
00:37:27,662 --> 00:37:31,499
Smaller business. Much more manageable.
Without livestock.

574
00:37:31,583 --> 00:37:34,377
-He's mined the area.
-They're gonna kill it.

575
00:37:34,461 --> 00:37:38,840
They found that thing centuries ago
beneath the northern glacier.

576
00:37:39,507 --> 00:37:42,093
-Those pylons.
-In a circle.

577
00:37:42,260 --> 00:37:44,345
DONNA: The circle must be broken.

578
00:37:44,429 --> 00:37:46,473
Dampening the telepathic field.

579
00:37:46,556 --> 00:37:49,684
Stopping the Ood from connecting
for 200 years.

580
00:37:49,768 --> 00:37:52,771
And you, Ood Sigma,
you brought them here.

581
00:37:52,854 --> 00:37:54,439
I expected better.

582
00:37:54,522 --> 00:37:56,858
My place is at your side, sir.

583
00:37:58,151 --> 00:38:01,571
Still subservient. Good Ood.

584
00:38:02,655 --> 00:38:06,284
If that barrier thing's in place,
how come the Ood started breaking out?

585
00:38:06,367 --> 00:38:10,580
Maybe it's taken centuries to adapt,
subconscious reaching out.

586
00:38:10,663 --> 00:38:14,584
But the process was too slow,
had to be accelerated.

587
00:38:14,709 --> 00:38:17,962
You should never have given me
access to the controls, Mr Halpen.

588
00:38:18,046 --> 00:38:21,216
I lowered the barrier to its minimum.

589
00:38:21,299 --> 00:38:23,384
Friends of the Ood, sir.

590
00:38:23,468 --> 00:38:26,805
It's taken me 10 years to infiltrate
the company.

591
00:38:27,430 --> 00:38:29,390
And I succeeded.

592
00:38:30,391 --> 00:38:31,601
Yes.

593
00:38:32,560 --> 00:38:34,103
Yes, you did.

594
00:38:50,411 --> 00:38:53,122
You murdered him.

595
00:38:53,581 --> 00:38:55,583
Very observant, Ginger.

596
00:38:56,292 --> 00:38:57,752
Now then...

597
00:39:00,046 --> 00:39:02,841
Can't say I've ever shot anyone before.

598
00:39:03,633 --> 00:39:05,218
Can't say I'm gonna like it.

599
00:39:05,301 --> 00:39:09,889
But it's not exactly
a normal day, is it?

600
00:39:09,973 --> 00:39:11,182
Still...

601
00:39:11,266 --> 00:39:13,643
Would you like a drink, sir?

602
00:39:13,726 --> 00:39:17,564
I think hair loss is the least
of my problems right now, thanks.

603
00:39:17,647 --> 00:39:19,315
Please have a drink, sir.

604
00:39:19,399 --> 00:39:21,025
If...

605
00:39:21,109 --> 00:39:26,447
If you're gonna stand in their way,
I'll shoot you, too.

606
00:39:26,531 --> 00:39:28,658
Please have a drink, sir.

607
00:39:30,869 --> 00:39:34,956
Have... Have you poisoned me?

608
00:39:35,081 --> 00:39:37,625
Natural Ood must never kill sir.

609
00:39:37,750 --> 00:39:39,627
What is that stuff?

610
00:39:39,752 --> 00:39:42,463
Ood graft suspended in
a biological compound, sir.

611
00:39:42,589 --> 00:39:45,884
-What the hell does that mean?
-Oh, dear!

612
00:39:45,967 --> 00:39:47,302
Tell me!

613
00:39:47,385 --> 00:39:51,222
Funny thing, the subconscious.
Takes all sorts of shapes.

614
00:39:51,306 --> 00:39:55,310
Came out in the red eyes' revenge,
came out in the rabid Oods' anger,

615
00:39:55,393 --> 00:39:58,146
and then there was patience.

616
00:40:01,316 --> 00:40:04,986
All that intelligence and mercy
focused on Ood Sigma.

617
00:40:06,279 --> 00:40:08,656
How's the hair loss, Mr Halpen?

618
00:40:15,288 --> 00:40:16,581
What have you done?

619
00:40:16,664 --> 00:40:20,418
Oh, they've been preparing you
for a very long time.

620
00:40:21,336 --> 00:40:23,588
And now you're standing next to
the Ood brain.

621
00:40:23,713 --> 00:40:25,673
Mr Halpen, can you hear it?

622
00:40:25,798 --> 00:40:27,050
Listen.

623
00:40:29,052 --> 00:40:30,845
(MELODIC SINGING)

624
00:40:32,847 --> 00:40:34,891
What have you...

625
00:40:36,559 --> 00:40:38,353
I'm not...

626
00:41:16,140 --> 00:41:17,433
They...

627
00:41:18,434 --> 00:41:21,062
They turned him into an Ood?

628
00:41:21,604 --> 00:41:23,064
Yup.

629
00:41:24,232 --> 00:41:25,984
He's an Ood!

630
00:41:26,067 --> 00:41:27,777
I noticed.

631
00:41:27,902 --> 00:41:29,821
(MOANING)

632
00:41:37,036 --> 00:41:40,915
He has become Ood-kind,
and we will take care of him.

633
00:41:44,919 --> 00:41:48,756
It's weird. Being with you, I can't tell
what's right and what's wrong any more.

634
00:41:48,881 --> 00:41:50,758
It's better that way.

635
00:41:50,883 --> 00:41:53,344
People who know for certain
tend to be like Mr Halpen.

636
00:41:53,428 --> 00:41:54,512
Oh!

637
00:41:54,595 --> 00:41:56,014
(BEEPING)

638
00:41:56,097 --> 00:41:57,390
That's better.

639
00:41:57,473 --> 00:42:02,103
And now, Sigma,
would you allow me the honour?

640
00:42:02,520 --> 00:42:04,939
-It is yours, Doctor.
-Oh, yes!

641
00:42:05,023 --> 00:42:08,192
Stifled for 200 years, but not any more.

642
00:42:08,276 --> 00:42:10,069
The circle is broken.

643
00:42:10,153 --> 00:42:11,946
The Ood can sing!

644
00:42:12,030 --> 00:42:14,115
(MELODIC SINGING)

645
00:42:23,291 --> 00:42:25,251
I can hear it!

646
00:43:01,621 --> 00:43:03,790
DOCTOR: The message has gone out.

647
00:43:03,873 --> 00:43:07,210
That song resonated across the galaxies.
Everyone heard it.

648
00:43:07,335 --> 00:43:08,878
Everyone knows.

649
00:43:10,296 --> 00:43:12,757
The rockets are bringing them back.

650
00:43:12,840 --> 00:43:14,926
The Ood are coming home.

651
00:43:15,760 --> 00:43:19,097
We thank you, Doctor, Donna,
friends of Ood-kind.

652
00:43:19,180 --> 00:43:21,766
And what of you now? Will you stay?

653
00:43:21,849 --> 00:43:23,643
There is room in the song for you.

654
00:43:23,726 --> 00:43:27,647
Oh, I... I've sort of got
a song of my own, thanks.

655
00:43:28,314 --> 00:43:30,775
I think your song must end soon.

656
00:43:31,901 --> 00:43:33,194
Meaning?

657
00:43:33,319 --> 00:43:35,196
Every song must end.

658
00:43:36,197 --> 00:43:37,365
Yeah.

659
00:43:38,241 --> 00:43:41,994
Um, what about you?
You still want to go home?

660
00:43:42,495 --> 00:43:44,330
No. Definitely not.

661
00:43:45,373 --> 00:43:46,791
Then we'll be off.

662
00:43:46,874 --> 00:43:50,002
-Take this song with you.
-We will.

663
00:43:50,086 --> 00:43:51,504
Always.

664
00:43:51,587 --> 00:43:55,383
And know this, Doctor, Donna,
you will never be forgotten.

665
00:43:55,508 --> 00:43:58,302
Our children will sing of
the Doctor, Donna,

666
00:43:58,386 --> 00:44:00,555
and our children's children,

667
00:44:00,638 --> 00:44:05,434
and the wind and the ice and the snow
will carry your names forever.

668
00:44:24,412 --> 00:44:26,414
Doctor? It's Martha.

669
00:44:27,373 --> 00:44:29,167
And I'm bringing you back to Earth.

670
00:44:29,584 --> 00:44:32,420
Yesterday, 52 people died
in identical circumstances,

671
00:44:32,503 --> 00:44:34,964
right across the world,
in 11 different time zones.

672
00:44:35,214 --> 00:44:37,175
And you think ATMOS is alien?

673
00:44:37,258 --> 00:44:39,051
It's our job to investigate
that possibility.

674
00:44:39,135 --> 00:44:40,386
Who are you?

675
00:44:40,469 --> 00:44:43,514
I am General Staal of
the 10th Sontaran Battle Fleet.

676
00:44:43,598 --> 00:44:44,891
We have an intruder!

677
00:44:44,974 --> 00:44:46,851
MARTHA: Operation Blue Sky
is go, go, go.

678
00:44:46,934 --> 00:44:50,229
Is that what you did to her?
Turned her into a soldier?

679
00:44:50,313 --> 00:44:51,564
MARTHA: Is that...

680
00:44:51,689 --> 00:44:52,732
Sontaran!

681
00:44:52,815 --> 00:44:54,942
Stare into the face of death!

